<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_a3e96f73-e43b-452d-bccf-3c10ef500293" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="TAS"><sptc>C4D2</sptc><title id="_a03854c4-a0dc-40a2-bd88-9452569c03f2">General requirements</title><archive-num>2019: Tas H2.2</archive-num><subclause id="_28a9d92a-b9d7-43c3-ac9e-97d324b365ac" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_7a6acabd-305d-4e08-8b36-d525a9c97a1d">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Where pre-treatment facilities are installed, they must comply with the requirements of—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_f7978192-84d5-4d85-a05f-5b118a06439c">the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1376_4.2.0.xml#_12d6153c-4986-4856-80c0-e21bb57af12f" id="_99896197-60d6-430e-a0ac-42df343bc799" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Network Utility Operator</xref> (where applicable); and</li><li id="_80c202d2-f2db-40eb-b4f5-5c8927887565">occupational health and safety; and</li><li id="_03275d94-c55f-4aad-bd78-d22a259c0b2a">dangerous goods management; and</li><li id="_04701a54-6717-4db9-af44-26d42dffd9bc">environmental protection.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_a00c3498-03e3-4a43-9e8a-4ffae1a974f1" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_5e0da0ed-cb22-40f2-b6bb-d971b95b345e">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>A liquid trade waste system that discharges to a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1376_4.2.0.xml#_12d6153c-4986-4856-80c0-e21bb57af12f" id="_776fb4af-88c8-4196-b9d5-858d3da86c83" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Network Utility Operator's</xref> sewerage system after pre-treatment must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_a15f7d88-680f-4ab1-905e-37e53cbce454">be capable of discharging liquid trade waste at a quality set under a Consent to Discharge issued for that equipment or system by the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1376_4.2.0.xml#_12d6153c-4986-4856-80c0-e21bb57af12f" id="_4a3daed5-48fe-4eda-bbd1-10e3c6a75da0" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Network Utility Operator</xref>; and</li><li id="_45fe37bd-da3e-4ebe-a125-6316e7a61f93">the sanitary drainage system must comply with:<ol><li>AS/NZS 3500.2; and</li><li>the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1376_4.2.0.xml#_12d6153c-4986-4856-80c0-e21bb57af12f" id="_c67d87ab-3483-4828-bedf-7434421bcca2" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Network Utility Operator's</xref> guidelines, insofar as the provisions relate to the system.</li></ol></li></ol></subclause><callout id="_dfedbabd-efac-4be2-8e04-14516ebaddb0"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><title id="_3b279833-643b-4199-b385-f898cf08ad3c">Cross-volume considerations</title><p><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/2_0.26.0.xml#_494d6510-5f84-496e-85cd-4d536f538b53" id="_061c2bb9-c5c6-47ed-afa1-a72b93fc99b6" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-part">Part B1</xref> of NCC Volume One sets out requirements relevant to the excavation of pipework adjacent to a building and footings for the purpose of installing liquid trade waste systems in Class 2 to Class 9 buildings.</p></callout></clause>